                            <comment id="13821478" author="slebresne" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 16:14:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Either that has been fixed in the current cassandra-2.0 tip or I&apos;ll need complete information to reproduce. I&apos;ve added the following dtest: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/riptano/cassandra-dtest/commit/971c4d629a8524205d7bedc1f49315be043a6ceb&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/riptano/cassandra-dtest/commit/971c4d629a8524205d7bedc1f49315be043a6ceb&lt;/a&gt; and tried doing:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&amp;gt; ccm node1 stress -n 10001
...
&amp;gt; ccm node1 cqlsh
Connected to test at 127.0.0.1:9160.
[cqlsh 4.1.0 | Cassandra 2.0.2-SNAPSHOT | CQL spec 3.1.1 | Thrift protocol 19.38.0]
Use HELP for help.
cqlsh&amp;gt; use &quot;Keyspace1&quot;;
cqlsh:Keyspace1&amp;gt; SELECT COUNT(*) FROM &quot;Standard1&quot; LIMIT 10002;

 count
-------
 10001

(1 rows)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All of that seems to be working fine as far as I can tell.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13821550" author="thattolleyguy" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 17:21:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If I don&apos;t use a limit on the select statement throws the exception.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;cqlsh:Keyspace1&amp;gt; select count(*) from &quot;Standard1&quot; limit 10002;

 count
-------
 10002

(1 rows)

cqlsh:Keyspace1&amp;gt; select count(*) from &quot;Standard1&quot;;
TSocket read 0 bytes
cqlsh:Keyspace1&amp;gt; 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13823692" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 15 Nov 2013 14:34:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, this is due to the fact that SP.getRangeSlice might return more results than asked (due to reconciliation, you need &amp;gt; 1 node) which was confusing the pager logic. Attaching patch so that the pager trim the result in that case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13829538" author="iamaleksey" created="Fri, 22 Nov 2013 01:07:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13829766" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 22 Nov 2013 07:47:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
